[{"Timecode":"","Caption":"{QTtext}{width:960}{textColor:65280,65280,65280}{justify:center}{timescale:1000}{backColor:0,0,0}{plain}{font:Verdana}{size:20}\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:00.016]","Caption":"\nIf everyone preformed great all the time,\nthere wouldn't be much need for leaders.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:05.300]","Caption":"\nIn reality of course there are plenty of\nperformance problems you have to address.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:09.430]","Caption":"\nMost professionals don't enjoy this aspect\nof leadership, but the best\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:13.630]","Caption":"\nleaders never back away from the hard\naspects of the job.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:17.430]","Caption":"\nHaving said that, you're busy and you cant\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:19.740]","Caption":"\nintervene to fix and coach people all the\ntime.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:22.380]","Caption":"\nI want you to get the most bang for your\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:25.130]","Caption":"\nintervention buck.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:26.230]","Caption":"\nThink through the following two questions\nand they'll help you make the right call.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:31.530]","Caption":"\nFirst, is the behavior in question best\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:33.810]","Caption":"\ndescribed as a pattern or a one-time\nevent?\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:36.668]","Caption":"\nUnless the one-time incident represents a\nvery large problem, you\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:41.340]","Caption":"\nwant to look for a patter of performance\ndeviations before intervening.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:45.890]","Caption":"\nNext, is the area of performance in\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:47.590]","Caption":"\nquestion truly important or of minor\nimportance?\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:50.745]","Caption":"\nSometimes, you might be bothered when\nsomeone doesn't do\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:53.730]","Caption":"\nsomething exactly the way you like it to\nbe done.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:56.450]","Caption":"\nFair enough.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:57.790]","Caption":"\nBut try to resist intervening until the\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:00:59.880]","Caption":"\ndeviation is actually affecting\nproductivity or morale.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:04.030]","Caption":"\nAfter considering these questions, it's\ntime to make the call.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:07.560]","Caption":"\nIf you choose to intervene, respect the\nemployee by having a private conversation.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:12.410]","Caption":"\nBe very positive, but be clear in\nexplaining what you've observed.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:16.570]","Caption":"\nYour goal is to begin a dialogue with the\nemployee so\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:19.330]","Caption":"\nyou can start to look for the root cause\nof the behavior.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:22.670]","Caption":"\nAnd don't forget it's possible you could\nbe part of the problem.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:26.170]","Caption":"\nWho knows?\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:26.830]","Caption":"\nMaybe the instructions you gave were\nunclear or you\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:29.460]","Caption":"\ndidn't give them the best resources to do\nthe job.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:32.350]","Caption":"\nIn general, you want to understand whether\nthe performance problem is\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:35.670]","Caption":"\nbetter explained by a lack of ability or a\nlack of motivation.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:40.070]","Caption":"\nOne or the other is typically the culprit,\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:42.150]","Caption":"\nbut don't assume you know which one it is.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:44.420]","Caption":"\nLet good conversation uncover which one is\nthe source.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:48.840]","Caption":"\nIf the issue is about ability, you need to\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:50.800]","Caption":"\nthink about solutions that increase\nability, including training or coaching.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:55.770]","Caption":"\nIf the issue is motivation, you might\nthink\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:01:57.900]","Caption":"\nmore deeply about the interpersonal\nsupport you're providing.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:01.840]","Caption":"\nYou also have to consider whether or not\nthe person's\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:04.100]","Caption":"\nskills are sufficiently aligned with the\nneeds of the work.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:07.800]","Caption":"\nIn other words, they might be in the wrong\nrole.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:09.670]","Caption":"\nOr it might be possible their current role\nis too narrow or too wide.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:15.020]","Caption":"\nAfter agreeing on an initial solution,\nalso be sure\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:17.860]","Caption":"\nto carefully clarify the consequences if\nthe behavior doesn't change.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:22.570]","Caption":"\nThey need to know that continued poor\nperformance is not an option.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:26.960]","Caption":"\nLast but not least keep your eyes\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:28.810]","Caption":"\nopen, and remember to unobtrusively\nmonitor their progress.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:33.340]","Caption":"\nCorrecting performance problems can be\ndifficult, but when\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:36.349]","Caption":"\ndone right, it can also be very rewarding.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:39.392]","Caption":"\nFollow these tips, and you've got a great\nshot to get your employee back on track.\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:43.920]","Caption":"\n(BLANK_AUDIO)\n\n"},{"Timecode":"[00:02:43.920]","Caption":"\n\n"}]